item.title: PI 602 Animations Error
item.dc:creator: @JustChillBro JustChillBro
item.description:
@JustChillBro wrote:

I was trying to add 602 animations from this tutorial on rune-server and I get this error.

client.java:2862: error: cannot find symbol Class36.method529(onDemandData.buffer); ^ symbol: method method529(byte[]) location: class Class36 Note: client.java uses unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 1 error Press any key to continue . . .
I redownloaded the client again and that same method is in there but for some reason its giving me a error.
EDIT:
Fixed the error but now when I try to login I get this error in the cmd prompt:

13798 NPC.DAT : 1489108188 Called method225 NPC.IDX : 1489126980 Called method225 602 GFX Amount: 2617 Error: T1 - 123,0 - 36,36 Exception in thread "Thread-5" java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: 103 at Class36.method531(Class36.java:300) at Model.method470(Model.java:796) at ObjectDef.method581(ObjectDef.java:248) at ObjectDef.method578(ObjectDef.java:118) at Animable_Sub5.getRotatedModel(Animable_Sub5.java:41) at Animable.method443(Animable.java:10) at WorldController.method314(WorldController.java:1530) at WorldController.method313(WorldController.java:1021) at client.method146(client.java:12068) at client.drawGameScreen(client.java:8228) at client.processDrawing(client.java:8939) at RSApplet.run(RSApplet.java:108) at client.run(client.java:4758) at java.lang.Thread.run(Unknown Source)
